cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.LG 

This paper discusses the subtasks of abusive language detection and analysis, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and data annotation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses cyberbullying and online abuse, which could place it under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
